  "intro": "Imagine you’re selling a seat at a sold‑out concert. You can’t hand the buyer a physical object that they can keep forever – you’re selling a promise, a right to experience something unforgettable. In this quick 5‑minute lesson, we’ll uncover why a ticket is an intangible product, explore how it differs from a traditional physical good, and see how a Customer Relationship Management (CRM) system works like a navigator guiding your customers from first click to post‑event follow‑up. By the end, you’ll be able to name five key differences between tickets and tangible items, articulate three core traits of intangible products in your own words, and use the navigator analogy to explain CRM’s vital role in ticket sales.",
